🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ OSI Model (Most Important for Interviews)
Simple Idea

OSI model divides communication into 7 layers, like a step-by-step process.

Mental Model (Sending a Courier 📦)

When you send a parcel:

Write message → Application

Format it → Presentation

Start communication → Session

Break into packets → Transport

Decide route → Network

Physical transfer → Data Link

Send via wire → Physical

The 7 Layers
Layer	Function
Application	User interaction
Presentation	Format/encryption
Session	Connection management
Transport	Reliable delivery
Network	Routing
Data Link	Error detection
Physical	Actual transmission
Why It Works

Breaking into layers makes systems:

modular

easier to debug

easier to design

Connection to Programming

Think of functions calling functions:

sendData() → processData() → routeData() → transmit()

Each layer = one responsibility.

Memory Trick 🧠

All People Seem To Need Data Processing

(A-P-S-T-N-D-P)

2️⃣ TCP vs UDP (VERY IMPORTANT)
Simple Idea

Two ways to send data:

TCP → reliable

UDP → fast

Mental Model

📦 TCP = Courier with tracking

ensures delivery

resends if lost

slower

🚀 UDP = Normal post (no tracking)

no guarantee

faster

Key Differences
Feature	TCP	UDP
Reliability	Yes	No
Speed	Slower	Faster
Connection	Required	Not required
Real Examples

TCP → websites, email

UDP → video streaming, gaming

Why It Works

Different applications need different priorities:

Banking → reliability

Live video → speed

Memory Trick

TCP = Trust (reliable)
UDP = Ultra fast (but risky)

3️⃣ Packet Switching vs Circuit Switching
Packet Switching (Internet uses this)
Idea

Data is broken into small packets and sent independently.

Mental Model

Sending a book as:

separate pages

each page takes different route

reassembled at destination

Why It Works

efficient

no dedicated path needed

scalable

Circuit Switching (Old telephone system)
Idea

A dedicated path is established before communication.

Mental Model

Phone call:

connection reserved

no interruption

fixed path

Comparison
Feature	Packet	Circuit
Path	Dynamic	Fixed
Efficiency	High	Low
Example	Internet	Telephone
Memory Trick

Packet = pieces
Circuit = single path

4️⃣ IP Address & MAC Address
IP Address

Logical address

Used for global identification

Example:

192.168.1.1
MAC Address

Physical address

Unique to device hardware

Example:

00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E
Mental Model

Think of delivery system:

IP → City address

MAC → House number

Why It Works

IP helps route data across networks

MAC ensures delivery within local network

Memory Trick

IP = Internet identity
MAC = Machine identity

🌍 Social Networks
5️⃣ Centrality (Who is Important?)

Centrality measures importance of a node.

Types

Degree Centrality

Closeness Centrality

Betweenness Centrality

Mental Model

In a college:

Popular student → high centrality

Connector between groups → very important

Why It Works

Helps identify:

influencers

key spreaders

important nodes

Memory Trick

Centrality = Importance score

6️⃣ Closeness Centrality
Idea

Measures how quickly a node can reach others.

Mental Model

Student who can reach everyone quickly:

knows all groups

communicates fast

Why It Matters

Used in:

information spreading

network optimization

Memory Trick

Closer → Faster reach

7️⃣ Betweenness Centrality
Idea

Measures how often a node acts as a bridge.

Mental Model

Friend who connects two friend groups.

If removed → groups disconnect.

Why It Matters

identifies critical nodes

useful in network security

Memory Trick

Bridge node = High betweenness

8️⃣ Small World Network
Idea

Everyone is connected through very few steps.

Famous Concept

“6 Degrees of Separation”

Mental Model

You → friend → friend → celebrity

Within few steps → everyone connects.

Why It Works

Real networks are:

highly connected

short paths

Memory Trick

Big network, small distance

🎯 10 Most Asked Computer Network Interview Questions
1️⃣ What is OSI model?

A 7-layer architecture for network communication.

2️⃣ Difference between OSI and TCP/IP?

OSI → theoretical model
TCP/IP → practical model used in internet

3️⃣ What is TCP?

Reliable, connection-oriented protocol.

4️⃣ What is UDP?

Fast, connectionless protocol.

5️⃣ What is packet switching?

Breaking data into packets and sending separately.

6️⃣ What is circuit switching?

Dedicated communication path.

7️⃣ What is IP address?

Logical identifier for a device.

8️⃣ What is MAC address?

Physical hardware address.

9️⃣ What is DNS?

Converts domain names to IP addresses.

🔟 What is a port number?

Identifies a specific process/service on a device.

Example:

HTTP → Port 80
HTTPS → Port 443
